Class HttpSessionsParam

java.lang.Object
org.parosproxy.paros.common.AbstractParam
org.zaproxy.zap.extension.httpsessions.HttpSessionsParam
All Implemented Interfaces:
Cloneable
public class HttpSessionsParam extends AbstractParam
The HttpSessionsParam is used to store the parameters (options) for the ExtensionHttpSessions and related classes.

    • getDefaultTokens

      public final List<HttpSessionToken> getDefaultTokens()
      Gets the default tokens.

      The list of default session tokens returned is read-only view of the internal default session tokens representation and any modifications will result in UnsupportedOperationException. No change should be done to the HttpSessionTokens contained in the list.

      Returns:
      the default tokens
